Combine half-and-half, water, salt, and potatoes in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 18 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Meanwhile, melt butter in a stockpot over medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic to pan; saute 3 minutes. Add mushrooms; saute 5 minutes. Add broth; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 6 minutes. Add potato mixture to mushroom mixture; puree in batches. Garnish with chopped fresh thyme if desired.